➜English Night｜The Little Match Girl（excerpt）
http://www.sohu.com/a/419140488_404517	46853
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size: 16px;"></span></strong><strong><span style="font-size: 16px;">The Little Match Girl（excerpt）</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span><strong><span style="font-size: 16px;">卖火柴的小女孩（节选）</span></strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span>By Hans Christian Andersen</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span>汉斯·克里斯汀·安徒生</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">She took one out - ratch! </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">她终于抽出了一根。哧！</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">How it spurted, how it burned! </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">火柴燃起来了，冒出火焰来了！</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">It was a warm clear flame, just like a little candle, when she held her hand round it. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">她把小手拢在火焰上。多么温暖多么明亮的火焰啊，简直像一支小小的蜡烛！</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://p4.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20200918/fc96b864910c4ce3a4a7cbc57b8ab101.png" /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">It was a wonderful light; the little girl thought she was sitting right before a great iron stove, with bright brass feet and brass mountings. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">这是一道奇异的火光！小女孩觉得自己好像坐在一个大火炉前面，火炉装着闪亮的铜脚和铜把手。</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">How beautifully the fire burned, how it warmed her. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">烧得旺旺的，暖烘烘的，多么舒服啊！</span></p>            <div class="lookall-box">
<div class="lookall-shadow"></div>
<section class="lookall">
<a href="javascript:;" class="show-all" id="showMore">
<em>展开全文</em>
</a>
</section>
</div>
<div class="hidden-content control-hide">
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">But, what was that? </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">哎，这是怎么回事呢？</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">The little girl stretched her feet out to warm them also, and the flame went out – the stove vanished – she had only the small stump of the burnt match in her hand.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">她刚把脚伸出去，想让脚也暖和一下，火柴灭了，火炉不见了。她坐在那儿，手里只有一根烧过了的火柴梗。</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">A new match was rubbed against the wall; it burned, it gave a beautiful light, and where the light fell on the wall it became transparent like a veil. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">她又擦了一根。火柴燃起来了，发出亮光来了。亮光落在墙上，那儿忽然变得像薄纱那么透明。</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">She could see right into the room, where the table was covered with a bright white cloth, and on it a fine china dinner-service; the roast goose, stuffed with prunes and apples, was steaming beautifully. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">她可以一直看到屋里，桌上铺着雪白的台布，摆着精致的盘子和碗，肚子里填满了苹果和梅子的烤鹅正冒着香气。</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://p4.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20200918/3e8cf629b9a448e38473b896318a3963.jpeg" /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">But, what was still more delightful, the goose jumped from the dish and waddled along the floor, with knife and fork in its back, straight towards the poor girl, when the match went out, and there was only the thick cold wall to be seen.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">更妙的是这只鹅从盘子里跳下来，背上插着刀叉，摇摇摆摆地在地板上走着，一直向这个穷苦的小女孩走来。这时候，火柴又灭了，她面前只有一堵又厚又冷的墙。</span></p>
<p><span>&gt;</span><span>&gt;</span><span>&gt;</span><span>&gt;</span></p>
